The paper proposes a method for improving the performance of 1-D convolutional layers in deep neural networks for time series classification tasks by aligning the convolution filter and input using an algorithm similar to Dynamic Time Warp. This work involves machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and natural language processing (cs.CL) as the proposed layer can be integrated with other typical layers to compose deep artificial neural networks.
